OL,3,CThe chancellor's choice between
OL,4,CNational Insurance and income tax cuts
OL,6,FThe second would do the same, but
OL,7,Fwould also hand additional cash to
OL,8,Fcore Tory supporters, namely
OL,9,Fpensioners and those with investment
OL,10,Fincome (from property rentals, share
OL,11,Fdividends, interest in savings and so
OL,12,Fon).
OL,14,FInevitably therefore cutting the rate
OL,15,Fof income tax costs #2bn a year more
OL,16,Fthan cutting NI for each penny
OL,17,Freduction. So bribing more potential
OL,18,Fvoters isn't cheap.
